Smart Link DSP library — redistribution notice
==============================================

The file vm/slmodemd/dsplibs.o is a proprietary closed-source object
file from Smart Link Ltd. that implements the modem data pumps used
by slmodemd. It contains no synthmodem code; we redistribute it
unmodified as part of the vendored slmodemd tree.

Origin
------
dsplibs.o is distributed with Smart Link's free "Soft Modem" binary
release, which Smart Link authorized to be included in the Debian
sl-modem-daemon source package under the following terms:

  "Smart Link hereby grants permission to free-redistribute this
   binary [dsplibs.o] as part of the sl-modem-daemon package."

The file we ship was sourced from the synexo/D-Modem upstream at
commit 902c79aa36fa094c7513fa911b64f4fa8a0bf614, which in turn
obtained it from the same Debian package distribution chain.

Redistribution obligations
--------------------------
1. This file (licenses/DSPLIBS-NOTICE) must accompany every
   redistribution that includes dsplibs.o.
2. dsplibs.o is redistributed unmodified and with no claim of
   ownership by the synthmodem project.
3. This notice and the accompanying dsplibs.o must be kept together
   in any binary bundle.

Limitations we accept
---------------------
- No source is available, so we cannot rebuild it, patch bugs in it,
  or port it to architectures other than 32-bit i386.
- dsplibs.o is used only when the slmodemd backend is selected
  (config.modem.backend = 'slmodemd'). The default 'native' backend
  does not use it.

If the redistribution terms for dsplibs.o change in the future (or
are challenged), the slmodemd backend can be disabled by excluding
dsplibs.o and shipping only the native backend. The synthmodem
codebase itself does not depend on dsplibs.o at build time.
